The time has come to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house where nothing has been done, just a bit of decoration.
Remove the horrible electric fireplace and the hearth. Coffer the chimney, replace the damaged plaster and sand. Make a custom closet.
We always start with a quick sketch with a pencil...
The messy step is over.
I found several dead birds at the back of the conduit; completely dried up :(
Ready for the plastering next week
Happy with the little niche on the side
Insert the new closet here (it's not like we've already started designing it 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the radiator!
And we even thought to add a charming little ventilation hole to prevent the chimney from getting humid
The chimney sweep took care of installing the hat and the vent. It should be a bit safer for the crows nesting up there 🪺
The plasterer has finished. We'll install the subfloor tomorrow!
The underlayment is in place, I improvised a wood shavings extractor using a toilet paper roll as an attachment for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Part of the floorboards has been sorted and is ready to be installed. We're just taking a tea break
Well, progress was slow today due to super delicate cuts around the door frames to achieve a smooth transition to the hallway (which is also being installed). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Finished, but on the last stretch! The cherry on top: the immoveable obstacles to assembling the new bed. We will sleep well tonight!
Remaining tasks include installing the hallway floor, all trim. The interior designer is coming in a month, so until then, at home, it's all about plaster without finish
A quick DIY session in the evening to remove the lower sections of the door frames with a tenon saw/cutlass at the point where we want the floor to be perfectly adjusted.
The subfloor made of wood insulation in the hallway has also been installed
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then departure at 5am this morning to pick up Thing 1 at Heathrow, followed by a siesta and the final stretch for the hallway; trim installed. We will take care of sealing when the glue has dried.
